Brest Campus

Texte

Postal address:

   IMT Atlantique Bretagne-Pays de la Loire
   Campus de Brest
   Technopôle Brest-Iroise
   CS 83818
   29238 Brest cedex 03
   France
   Tél. +33 (0)2 29 00 11 11
   The reception is open from Monday to Friday from 7:45 am to 7 pm.
     __________________________________________________________________

Brest - a dynamic student city

   Brest has over 24,000 students in a population of 200,000 people.
   That's one of the highest ratios in France. With a university, nine
   Grandes Écoles and research centres, Brest, also known as "la Cité du
   Ponant", is vibrant with student life.

Linked to all Europe

   Brest's international airport, provides quick links to all major
   European cities.  Under an hour from Paris (ten flights per day), and
   one hour from Brussels and London, Brest is far from isolated.
   As for trains, there are eight high-speed trains (TGV) daily to Paris.

With its feet in the ocean,

   The Brest Campus, where all engineering students must spend at least a
   year, is without a doubt one of the most attractive in Europe.
   Everything here is designed to make student life easier.

   An arial view of Brest Campus
   an aerial view of Brest Campus
